			<center><b>Notice concerning services</b></center>

        	<p>Due to a labour disruption that began on September 1, 2011, there will be an impact 
            on levels of client services at MUA.</p>

              <p>The MUA reception and reference desk will maintain normal open hours.
              However, services to researchers will be diminished. Responses to research
              inquiries will take longer, our capacity to process orders for reproductions
              will be limited, delays in the retrieval of requests for records are
              expected.
              </p>
            
              <p>Onsite hours for consultation of archival records will be reduced.
              Clients wishing to consult original records may do so between the hours of
              2:00 p.m. to 4:30 p.m., Tuesday and Wednesday.
              </p>

			<p>We recommend researchers call 514-398-3772 or e-mail 
            <a href="mailto:refdesk.archives@mcgill.ca">refdesk.archives@mcgill.ca</a>
            for an appointment because walk-in services will be significantly reduced. Thank you for your patience.
